Only selected pages have been scanned.
Identification on preliminary pages (handwritten): Ellen Day Hale, 39 Highland St., Roxbury, Mass.; begun at Peekskill.
Includes sketches of people and landscapes, mostly in graphite, one in color. Also includes a few handwritten entries; lists and an entry with the heading "Leonard's journey to Port Judith."
Ellen Hale and Hale family papers
Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution
